    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Drawers or boxes fitted in a larger piece of furniture; frequently found in Medieval chests and sometimes in 16th- and 17th-century cupboards.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000011251/Edwards and Macquoid, Dictionary of English Furniture, 2d ed. (1983)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Laden of dozen die in een groter meubelstuk passen. Veelvuldig aangetroffen in middeleeuwse kisten en soms in 16e en 17e eeuwse kasten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Schubkästen oder Kästen in einem größeren Möbelstück, häufig in mittelalterlichen Truhen und manchmal in Schränken aus dem 16. und 17. Jahrhundert.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
